nks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret Aldborough was born about 1395, in Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with Robert Roucliffe. She died about 1394, at the age of 1."},"et":{"Abt 1395–Abt 1394":"umbes 1395–umbes 1394","1372–Male":"1372–Surnud","1415–1460":"1415–1460","1395–1394":"1395–1394","Abt 1395":"umbes 1395","1415":"1415","Abt 1394":"umbes 1394","1395":"1395","1394":"1394","1460":"1460","1372":"1372","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1395–Abt 1394":"noin 1395–noin 1394","1372–Male":"1372–Kuollut","1415–1460":"1415–1460","1395–1394":"1395–1394","Abt 1395":"noin 1395","1415":"1415","Abt 1394":"noin 1394","1395":"1395","1394":"1394","1460":"1460","1372":"1372","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1395–Abt 1394":"environ 1395–environ 1394","1372–Male":"1372–Décédé","1415–1460":"1415–1460","1395–1394":"1395–1394","Abt 1395":"environ 1395","1415":"1415","Abt 1394":"environ 1394","1395":"1395","1394":"1394","1460":"1460","1372":"1372","Yorkshire, England":"Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Margaret Aldborough est née environ 1395, à Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Robert Roucliffe. Elle est décédée environ 1394, à l’âge de 1 ans."},"de":{"Abt 1395–Abt 1394":"um 1395–um 1394","1372–Male":"1372–Verstorben","1415–1460":"1415–1460","1395–1394":"1395–1394","Abt 1395":"um 1395","1415":"1415","Abt 1394":"um 1394","1395":"1395","1394":"1394","1460":"1460","1372":"1372","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Margaret Aldborough wurde um 1395 in Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom geboren. Sie hatte mit Robert Roucliffe mindestens 1 Sohn. Sie starb um 1394 im Alter von 1 Jahre